ed Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"Littlefield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Littlefield Green in White Waltham, Berkshire. The placename derives from Old English <i>lȳtel</i> ‘little’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open country’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":29,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":38,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Littlefield was born in 1520, in Titchfield, Hampshire, England, her father, Stephen William Littlefield, was 40 and her mother, Margaret Clopton, was 33. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with William Austin. She died in 1567, in her hometown, at the age of 47, and was buried in Titchfield, Hampshire, England."},"et":{"1520–1567":"1520–1567","1500–1567":"1500–1567","1516–1567":"1516–1567","1545–1634":"1545–1634","1547–1623":"1547–1623","1548–1623":"1548–1623","1552–1567":"1552–1567","1480–1567":"1480–1567","1487–1550":"1487–1550","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","1558":"1558","1547":"1547","1623":"1623","1634":"1634","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1515":"umbes 1515","1487":"1487","1552":"1552","about 1567":"umbes 1567","15 Feb 1554":"28. veebruar 1547","2 May 1550":"2. mai 1550","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","1548":"1548","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Titchfield,Hampshire,England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1520–1567":"1520–1567","1500–1567":"1500–1567","1516–1567":"1516–1567","1545–1634":"1545–1634","1547–1623":"1547–1623","1548–1623":"1548–1623","1552–1567":"1552–1567","1480–1567":"1480–1567","1487–1550":"1487–1550","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","1558":"1558","1547":"1547","1623":"1623","1634":"1634","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1515":"noin 1515","1487":"1487","1552":"1552","about 1567":"noin 1567","15 Feb 1554":"28. helmikuuta 1547","2 May 1550":"2. toukokuuta 1550","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","1548":"1548","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Titchfield,Hampshire,England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1520–1567":"1520–1567","1500–1567":"1500–1567","1516–1567":"1516–156